cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a unified framework that jointly solves both person re-identification and camera network topology inference problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories. The paper also discusses security and privacy issues related to multi-camera networks, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset, which involves data collection and annotation, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category as well.
